values: Hi my name is Bucky. Yes, I know I've been surgically altered. But I am looking for some FINE honies in search of a good time. I like the big girls too. I am 1 year old this month. I have blue eyes and I work out. My favorite interests include long walks on the windowsill and reading newspapers. Oh yeah and attacking shit. So if you're looking for a good time you know where to find me.

The posse, just chilling: Me and Misty, she's all right I guess. She's the only bee-otch close to kicking my ass.: Here's a picture of me and Picabo listening to mommy tell us something. I was dubious as usual. Yup this picture speaks a thousand words. Nasty ass smelling dog. She's had a bath since, thank goodness.

Man, last night momy couldn't sleep very well. So she came over and grabbed me and held me like a baby. It was cool for about an hour. I slept in her arms.  Hey but only cause it was toasty bee-otch! I didn't say I LIKED it.
http://bucky-cat.livejournal.com/2256.html

So daddy is pretty mad at me today. Well its all his fault! Him and mommy were sleeping in and there was only a few bits of food in my bowl! So I went in there to teach them a lesson. Clearly the way to do this is to knock their shit on to the floor. 

So I knocked Daddy's glasses on to the floor. And when they were on the floor, I played with them and moved them and bit them repeatedly and ran away with them in my mouth. Haha! They were none the wiser! Their smooth roundness felt so delightful in my jaws. 

A few hours later I heard daddy scream pissed off. I think he called me a furless curse word, "shit-head." It ends up I left permanent marks all over his glasses and now he can't wear them cause he can't see. They look all wet he says. 

Serves him right bee-otch! Next time get your ass out of bed when I ask for food!
